        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 4:44AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 443 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lamar, or near Rockport, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockport, Lamar, Aransas Pass, Palm Harbor, Key Allegro, Holiday
Beach, Aransas National Wildlife Refuge, Copano Village, and Fulton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
